On Mon, 7 Apr 2003 tjaspers(-at-)ameripath.com wrote:

> 	Sorry for all the questions... but I'm going to have a lot in the
> next couple of months...

not a problem but remember a lot of this stuff is already in the type 2
library at www.type2.com

> 1) What type of motor oil do I use for my 1.8 motor? IE: 5W-30? 5W-40? or is
> it even 50 weight?

that is almost a religous argument but any quality motor oil will work, in
summer a 20-40 weight would probably be fine, (I run 15W-50 Mobil 1
synthetic in mine)

> 2) Is the Bosch distributor original equipment?

yes and no, it was a Bosch distributor but there are several different
models that were used, the 009 is commonly added later and is NOT correct
for any VW van

> 3) The car came with a standard 2-bbl carburetor (I believe), but we also
> got with the car, a dual carburetor set-up.. they're Webber carbs. It also
> came with a stack of books, etc. Obviously, I'm not planning on entering
> this bus in the 24 huers de Le Mans any time soon... but I was curious how
> much horsepower if any that would provide over the standard 2bbl carb it has
> now?

I run only Fuel Injection so I am not the person to ask about Carbs, but I
think VW only used Solex carbs in the bus engines

> 4) Do you guys know of anywhere that actually SELLS used glass? After
> looking at the price of refurbished side vents.. I'm wondering if I wouldn't
> just be better off purchasing whole windows for the rear and buying new
> gaskets. Of the places I looked.. they don't sell actual glass.

BustedBus sells used glass

> Last question... why do some of my windows have the Audi OOOO symbol on them
> and others do not? 

VW owns Audi 

Bob


